JOHANNESBURG - Orlando Pirates have the bragging rights for the Soweto derby after beating Kaizer Chiefs 3-1 at FNB Stadium on Saturday. READ:Â Stats and Bets: The Soweto Derby The much anticipated Soweto derby didn't disappoint as it saw four goals being netted on the day. The two teams were locked at 1-1 at halftime following goals from Thembinkosi Lorch and Leonardo Castro. But it was Luvuyo Memela who stole the day by netting a brace, giving Pirates a 3-1 win over arch rivals Chiefs. Pirates are now sitting at 49 points on the log table just four points adrift of log-leaders Mamelodi Sundowns. eNCA